        <type>u32</type>
        <definition>u32 XilSKey_CrcCalculation</definition>
        <argsstring>(const u8 *Key)</argsstring>
        <name>XilSKey_CrcCalculation</name>
        <param>
          <type>const u8 *</type>
          <declname>Key</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This function Calculates CRC value based on hexadecimal string passed. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Key</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the string contains AES key in hexadecimal of length less than or equal to 64.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>On Success returns the Crc of AES key value.</para></listitem><listitem><para>On failure returns the error code when string length is greater than 64</para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>If the length of the string provided is less than 64, this function appends the string with zeros. For calculation of AES key&apos;s CRC one can use u32 XilSKey_CrcCalculation(u8 *Key) API or reverse polynomial 0x82F63B78. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
